More than half of American citizens are overweight and one out of four is obese, according to the latest issue of Science.
New cases among Mexican Americans rose from 5.7 % in 1987 to 15.7 % in 1996.
Among non-Hispanic whites, new cases rose from 2.6 % to 9.4 % during the period.
Obesity contributes to over 300,000 excess deaths each year.
Next to smoking, obesity is the second-leading cause of preventable death in the United States, according to President George Blackburn of the American Society of Clinical Nutrition.
First, obesity must be recognized as the serious public health problem.
